<HEADLINE>
FT  07 APR 94 / Ecuador debt payment
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RAYMOND COLITT
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   QUITO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Ecuador yesterday announced it would resume interest payment on its Dollars
7bn (Pounds 4.7bn) foreign commercial debt, which it stopped servicing in
September 1992, Raymond Colitt writes from Quito. Though the initial payment
of Dollars 5m towards interest in arrears is only symbolic, Finance Minister
Cesar Robalino said it would allow negotiations with the commercial banks to
move ahead.
</TEXT>
<XX>
