FT  07 APR 94 / Honduras murder plot
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   TEGUCIGALPA
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The Honduran army says it is investigating a foiled plot to assassinate
President Carlos Roberto Reina and kidnap a businessman, Reuter reports from
Tegucigalpa. Lt Col Napoleon Santos, an army spokesman, said one of four men
implicated in the conspiracy had told the Interior Ministry that a Honduran
citizen with links to the drug trade had offered the group Dollars 400,000
to kill the president and more than Dollars 800,000 to kidnap the
businessman.
President Reina won the election in November and took office on January 27,
pledging to carry out a 'moral revolution' in Honduras, weed out corruption
and curb the army's power.
