FT  07 APR 94 / Bundesbank eases lending costs
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRISTOPHER PARKES
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   FRANKFURT
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The Bundesbank yesterday continued its gradual easing of lending costs by
shaving a further three basis points off the securities repurchase rate at
which it supplies financial markets with short-term funds. The move down to
5.73 per cent was seen as a further signal that reductions in the
internationally important 5.25 per cent discount lending rate could still be
expected. But analysts were divided on the timing. In the recent past the
German central bank has developed a knack for making cuts when markets least
expect them.
