<TEXT>
The Dutch prime minister, Mr Ruud Lubbers, cut short an official visit to
Indonesia and returned home last night in an effort to defuse differences
between his ruling Christian Democrat (CDA) party and the Labour coalition
partners, with a general election only one month away. The coalition today
