support for the CDA had plunged by a third since the 1989 elections to 19.5
per cent, putting it in last place among the four top parties now led by
Labour. The main beneficiaries of voter dissatisfaction have been D66, a
centrist party, the right-wing Liberals, and a number of smaller groups
