FT  06 APR 94 / London Stock Exchange: Other big moves
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By STEVE THOMPSON, JOEL KIBAZO and PETER JOHN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Housebuilding and construction group George Wimpey jumped 11 to 198p after
taking full control of its West of England and Welsh quarrying subsidiary
Wimpey Hobbs.
International Business Communications rose 21 to 207p on a sharp upturn in
1993 profits. USM-quoted Proteus International, which announced a
one-for-seven cash call last week, slipped below the rights issue price to
close 7 off at 178p.
