</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By GILLIAN TETT
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   BRUSSELS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Expanding sales in the Asia Pacific market helped Barco, the Belgian
electronics group, push profits 22.7 per cent higher last year, writes
Gillian Tett in Brussels.
Profits after tax for 1993 were BFr1.1bn (Dollars 30.5m), up from BFr900m
the year before, and BFr600m in 1991. Total turnover rose by 4.1 per cent to
BFr10.5bn, up from BFr10.1bn in 1992.
