<HEADLINE>
FT  06 APR 94 / UK Company News: Stylo returns to black with Pounds 2.6m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID BLACKWELL
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Stylo, which owns the Barratts chain of shoe shops, returned to the black in
the year to January 29, exceeding City expectations with pre-tax profits of
Pounds 2.55m.
This compared with losses of Pounds 746,000 last time, struck after a Pounds
1.33m gain from sales of fixed assets. The latest figure included an
exceptional gain of Pounds 220,000.
Turnover increased to Pounds 116.5m (Pounds 105.5m). Operating profits
doubled to Pounds 6.92m (Pounds 3.47m).
Mr Michael Ziff, managing director, said the group was concentrating on
better products, improved merchandising and tighter control of expenses in
its core areas - Barratts, Instep sportswear outlets, and the golf and
equestrian wholesale business. During the year the group opened 25 new
branches and closed six.
Net borrowings fell by Pounds 4m to Pounds 39.9m, and net interest payable
dipped to Pounds 4.59m (Pounds 5.55m).
Earnings were 12.1p (losses of 4.01p). The single dividend is lifted to 4p
(3p). A 1-for-2 scrip issue is also proposed.
