<HEADLINE>
FT  06 APR 94 / Big increase in company start-ups
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
More than 12,000 companies were formed in Great Britain in March, the
highest monthly total since 1990. Figures from Jordans, the Bristol-based
information company, show that 12,638 companies were formed last month, a
6.4 per cent increase on March 1993.
March is traditionally a strong month for creation of companies because it
coincides with the end of the tax year. However, Jordans' figures show a
consistent growth trend. Company formations in the six months to March were
59,705 compared with 56,669 in the same period a year earlier, a 5.4 per
cent increase.
</TEXT>
