<HEADLINE>
FT  06 APR 94 / Business failures continue to rise
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The number of business failures has risen for the second month running,
reversing the trend of the past two years, says accountancy firm Touche
Ross.
Mr Ralph Preece, a Touche Ross corporate recovery specialist, said: 'We are
unlikely to see the widely expected fall in receiverships unless there is a
resurgence in economic confidence.'
The analysis of figures from the London and Edinburgh Gazettes shows there
were 262 receivership and administration appointments last month, a 5 per
cent increase on February's 248. The January figure was 163. However, the
year-on-year comparison still showed a fall from the 407 appointments in
March last year.
</TEXT>
