<HEADLINE>
FT  06 APR 94 / Doubt cast on personnel policies
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Human resource management, including employee involvement, single status for
all employees and performance pay, do not improve management-employee
relations, a study by Professor David Metcalf and Ms Sue Fernie of the
London School of Economics has found.
The study also finds that workplaces with a personnel specialist have worse
relations between management and labour than those without one.
</TEXT>
<XX>
Countries:-
</XX>
<CN>GBZ  United Kingdom, EC.
</CN>
<XX>
Industries:-
</XX>
