<HEADLINE>
FT  05 APR 94 / Company News (This Week): Construction group breathes again
 -Other companies
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Amec, the building and civil engineering company, will on Thursday announce
results for 1993 - a year which looks to have marked the turning point in
the UK construction recession. The company, which suffered more badly than
most contractors from its excursion into UK housebuilding, is expected to
have bounced back into the black. Analysts are forecasting pre-tax profits
of Pounds 22m-Pounds 25m, compared with a Pounds 87.5m loss after provisions
of Pounds 114.6m in 1992.
The market will be interested to hear Amec's view on the outlook for UK
contracting margins following the recent negative comments.
