to achieve a sales increase of 16 per cent to FFr2.85bn in 1993 from
FFr2.46bn in 1992.
Operating profits rose by 19 per cent to FFr406m from FFr341m over the same
period.
The board proposed raising the net dividend to FFr4.10 a share against the
payment of FFr3.70 in the previous year.
