FT  05 APR 94 / Fall in average hours worked
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Average hours worked fell slightly in the year to autumn 1993. This
underlines that in spite of the increase in part-time jobs, which has helped
reduce unemployment, there was no net increase in work last year, says a
Trades Union Congress analysis.
UK unemployment will fall by about 15,000 a month this year to reach 2.6m by
the end of the year, says a report by merchant bank Morgan Grenfell.
