<HEADLINE>
FT  05 APR 94 / Racial bias at Barclays alleged
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The Commission for Racial Equality has been asked by a union to investigate
allegations of racial bias in the selection of staff at Barclays Bank for
compulsory redundancy.
The Bifu banking union says that almost 17 per cent of 432 Barclays staff
selected for redundancy in London and the south-east are black or Asian.
This compares with an 11 per cent representation of ethnic minorities staff
overall in those areas.
The union call has been made as Barclays today begins hearing final appeals
against the redundancies.
